article.headline: Northeastern 51, New Hampshire 41
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Bennet Davis scored eight points and grabbed a career-high 19 rebounds to lead Northeastern to a 51-41 victory over New Hampshire Monday night. The Wildcats (1-8) trailed through the entire second half, but closed within three points several times. Each time they got close, the Huskies (3-6) answered. The last time New Hampshire got within three, at 41-38 with 6:49 left, Northeastern scored the next 10 points to put the game away. Davis scored two baskets to key the game-clinching run. Northeastern's Adrian Martinez finished with 15 points and Bobby Kelly added 14. New Hampshire was led by Blagoj Janez who had 16 points and eight rebounds. Both teams struggled offensively in the first half. New Hampshire shot 21 percent and had seven turnovers and just six baskets. Northeastern wasn't much better, shooting 30 percent, but managed to grab a 23-15 halftime lead. The Huskies went on a 12-2 run in the first half to take a 17-7 lead they never relinquished. For the game, Northeastern shot 35 percent, while New Hampshire shot 26 percent.
